WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.190
Well, good evening family. Thank you for

00:00:03.200 --> 00:00:05.190
joining me again tonight. We're going to

00:00:05.200 --> 00:00:06.830
pray and go over some of

00:00:06.840 --> 00:00:08.710
the things that have happened in

00:00:08.720 --> 00:00:10.390
the news

00:00:10.400 --> 00:00:14.110
in the last 48 hours or so. It's

00:00:14.120 --> 00:00:15.910
been a good weekend. I pray you've had a

00:00:15.920 --> 00:00:17.470
wonderful weekend. The weather's been

00:00:17.480 --> 00:00:19.870
nice. We've gotten some rain,

00:00:19.880 --> 00:00:22.670
and so, giving Jesus all the glory for

00:00:22.680 --> 00:00:24.590
the rain. Isn't it wonderful? Things

00:00:24.600 --> 00:00:27.230
start to get really green whenever the

00:00:27.240 --> 00:00:28.710
rain comes.

00:00:28.720 --> 00:00:32.350
I love it. The flowers,

00:00:32.350 --> 00:00:32.360
everything—the

00:00:32.360 --> 00:00:33.910
animals love it. Everything gets

00:00:33.920 --> 00:00:34.950
happy

00:00:34.960 --> 00:00:37.070
for the rain.

00:00:37.080 --> 00:00:38.710
Father, we thank you for all the rain

00:00:38.720 --> 00:00:40.550
that we've had. Thank you for all

00:00:40.560 --> 00:00:42.350
the rain we have in the forecast this

00:00:42.360 --> 00:00:45.350
week. We're so grateful for all the rain

00:00:45.360 --> 00:00:47.270
that you've given us. And I thank you

00:00:47.280 --> 00:00:50.070
that it's going to rain from sea to

00:00:50.080 --> 00:00:53.030
shining sea. We call in the rain. We

00:00:53.040 --> 00:00:55.510
thank you, Lord, that the drought is

00:00:55.520 --> 00:00:59.510
broken in the name of Jesus. We call it in

00:00:59.520 --> 00:01:02.710
again this week already;

00:01:02.720 --> 00:01:04.390
we call it in from the north, the

00:01:04.400 --> 00:01:06.790
south, east, and the west. We thank you, Lord,

00:01:06.800 --> 00:01:10.150
that the rain is coming on

00:01:10.160 --> 00:01:11.550
the jet stream as

00:01:11.550 --> 00:01:11.560
the low-pressure

00:01:11.560 --> 00:01:13.710
system is bringing it forth.

00:01:13.720 --> 00:01:15.390
But not only that, Father, we thank you,

00:01:15.400 --> 00:01:17.750
Lord, that it stalls out and just keeps

00:01:17.760 --> 00:01:20.590
dumping on our area. I thank you, Lord,

00:01:20.600 --> 00:01:22.550
that we would have enough to fill up our

00:01:22.560 --> 00:01:25.070
lakes, our ponds, our streams, our

00:01:25.080 --> 00:01:27.710
rivers, and Father, our reservoirs.

00:01:27.720 --> 00:01:29.790
Father, we thank you, Lord, that we have

00:01:29.800 --> 00:01:32.470
at least five inches this week in Jesus'name

00:01:32.470 --> 00:01:32.480
to

00:01:32.480 --> 00:01:35.110
get out of the deficit.

00:01:35.120 --> 00:01:37.030
Everybody say amen on that. You agree

00:01:37.040 --> 00:01:39.590
for your area because you don't just

00:01:39.600 --> 00:01:41.790
stop whenever you just get a little bit.

00:01:41.800 --> 00:01:43.550
That's the beginning; whenever you

00:01:43.560 --> 00:01:45.630
make it a greasy spot, you keep praying

00:01:45.640 --> 00:01:47.470
and calling the rain in in the

00:01:47.480 --> 00:01:49.430
spring. Well, Brandon, isn't it

00:01:49.430 --> 00:01:49.440
supposed to

00:01:49.440 --> 00:01:52.190
rain in the spring? Yes,

00:01:52.200 --> 00:01:54.430
but we had a major drought

00:01:54.440 --> 00:01:56.910
and we have to catch up.

00:01:56.920 --> 00:01:58.470
And so, for

00:01:58.470 --> 00:01:58.480
those

00:01:58.480 --> 00:02:01.630
of you

00:02:01.630 --> 00:02:01.640
who

00:02:01.640 --> 00:02:03.510
are having a lot of rain, don't take it

00:02:03.520 --> 00:02:06.710
for granted because fires are terrible when

00:02:06.710 --> 00:02:06.720
everything's

00:02:06.720 --> 00:02:09.109
burning up

00:02:09.119 --> 00:02:11.030
and you go, 'Man, we've got to have rain

00:02:11.040 --> 00:02:12.390
quick.'All

00:02:12.400 --> 00:02:15.030
right. So, okay, we have a lot of

00:02:15.040 --> 00:02:18.350
news here, Braden.

00:02:18.360 --> 00:02:20.830
This is where I'm at with... that's

00:02:20.840 --> 00:02:22.670
the chat.

00:02:22.680 --> 00:02:26.390
I don't want to see it.

00:02:26.400 --> 00:02:29.430
It moves in my

00:02:29.440 --> 00:02:30.750
eye whenever I see all those people

00:02:30.760 --> 00:02:32.030
talking.

00:02:37.520 --> 00:02:40.870
I want to say this. Oh, so we see the

00:02:40.870 --> 00:02:40.880
Sooners

00:02:40.880 --> 00:02:43.670
come out. Do you remember when I

00:02:43.680 --> 00:02:47.350
told you Japan will be the Sooner

00:02:47.360 --> 00:02:50.870
concerning crypto? Japan, South

00:02:50.870 --> 00:02:50.880
Korea—I

00:02:50.880 --> 00:02:53.070
said they will be the ones that implement

00:02:53.080 --> 00:02:55.710
things before America.

00:02:55.720 --> 00:02:58.630
And you'll start to see Japan

00:02:58.640 --> 00:03:01.830
implement the crypto laws and really

00:03:01.840 --> 00:03:05.390
try to go after it like

00:03:05.400 --> 00:03:07.870
America will in the days ahead. But I

00:03:07.880 --> 00:03:10.590
called them the Sooners. And I said, 'I saw

00:03:10.600 --> 00:03:12.470
the Boomer Schooner wagon.'If you're

00:03:12.480 --> 00:03:14.790
familiar with OU

00:03:16.560 --> 00:03:18.949
college football, they have a

00:03:18.949 --> 00:03:18.959
Schooner

00:03:18.959 --> 00:03:20.110
wagon. Well, every time they make a

00:03:20.120 --> 00:03:22.630
touchdown, they run out

00:03:22.640 --> 00:03:25.509
that wagon and celebrate the touchdown.

00:03:25.519 --> 00:03:27.350
And I said, 'This is what you're about

00:03:27.360 --> 00:03:29.910
to see.'I said, 'I saw Sooners coming

00:03:29.920 --> 00:03:32.870
across Japan and South Korea in the days

00:03:32.880 --> 00:03:34.350
ahead.'So

00:03:34.360 --> 00:03:37.910
Braden said, 'Daddy, the

00:03:37.920 --> 00:03:40.030
word is coming to pass.'Do you see it?

00:03:40.040 --> 00:03:41.070
Yeah.

00:03:41.080 --> 00:03:45.070
Is something wrong? Right. Okay.

00:03:45.080 --> 00:03:47.070
See this article

00:03:47.080 --> 00:03:48.990
right here? I don't know—some of this

00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:50.870
stuff, you have to be careful. There are a

00:03:50.880 --> 00:03:53.070
lot of scammers, but this is a good one.

00:03:53.080 --> 00:03:54.710
Braden says,

00:03:54.720 --> 00:03:58.910
'Okay, Japan officially approves bill to

00:03:58.920 --> 00:04:01.630
recognize cryptocurrency

00:04:01.640 --> 00:04:04.950
as a financial

00:04:04.950 --> 00:04:04.960
asset.'The

00:04:04.960 --> 00:04:07.470
Sooners. Ain't that neat? I

00:04:07.480 --> 00:04:08.870
thought that was so cool. I said, 'Look,

00:04:08.880 --> 00:04:10.949
Lord, it's happening.'Just like you

00:04:10.959 --> 00:04:15.510
said, Japan is announcing their recognition

00:04:15.510 --> 00:04:15.520
of

00:04:15.520 --> 00:04:18.190
cryptocurrency. The Sooners

00:04:18.200 --> 00:04:20.069
are at work. They're sending out

00:04:20.079 --> 00:04:21.910
the wagon.

00:04:21.920 --> 00:04:25.430
Here we go. Then we have the little

00:04:25.440 --> 00:04:29.270
gray-headed guy saying about America and

00:04:29.280 --> 00:04:31.430
Coinbase coming out and

00:04:31.440 --> 00:04:33.430
saying it's time to get it done. Do

00:04:33.440 --> 00:04:35.510
you have that? No.

00:04:35.520 --> 00:04:37.670
Oh, you don't? Okay. Do you have

00:04:37.680 --> 00:04:42.110
anything about...

00:04:42.120 --> 00:04:44.190
well, I thought that's what

00:04:44.200 --> 00:04:46.790
we were talking about. I'm sorry.

00:04:46.800 --> 00:04:48.310
I've been exercising. I've been out

00:04:48.320 --> 00:04:49.710
trying to do walks. So, I haven't

00:04:49.710 --> 00:04:49.720
had

00:04:49.720 --> 00:04:51.350
time to talk to Braden before it

00:04:51.360 --> 00:04:53.710
got dark because I'm trying to

00:04:53.720 --> 00:04:54.950
get this weight down as quickly as

00:04:54.960 --> 00:04:58.030
possible. I've gotten 25

00:04:58.040 --> 00:05:00.150
going on 30

00:05:00.150 --> 00:05:00.160
lbs

00:05:00.160 --> 00:05:01.270
off

00:05:01.280 --> 00:05:03.190
and I'm giving God all the glory for it.

00:05:03.200 --> 00:05:04.950
You know, the older I get,

00:05:04.960 --> 00:05:07.030
it seems... when I was in my 20s, it

00:05:07.040 --> 00:05:08.790
fell off a lot faster,

00:05:08.800 --> 00:05:10.190
but now

00:05:10.200 --> 00:05:12.470
I have to work harder, it seems. But

00:05:12.480 --> 00:05:14.470
that's all right. We're going to get it

00:05:14.480 --> 00:05:16.350
off. And I told Diana, I said, 'You know,

00:05:16.360 --> 00:05:17.470
just watching your calories and

00:05:17.470 --> 00:05:17.480
exercising.'I've

00:05:17.480 --> 00:05:19.070
been walking, taking

00:05:19.080 --> 00:05:20.110
walks,

00:05:20.120 --> 00:05:21.510
and

00:05:21.520 --> 00:05:25.150
it's fun, I guess.

00:05:25.160 --> 00:05:26.310
Woohoo!

00:05:27.160 --> 00:05:29.230
But Paisley likes it.

00:05:29.240 --> 00:05:30.390
All right,

00:05:30.400 --> 00:05:32.270
here is

00:05:32.280 --> 00:05:34.590
the guy that's over

00:05:34.600 --> 00:05:35.990
Coinbase.

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:39.230
We agree. So

00:05:39.240 --> 00:05:40.310
Scott—this

00:05:40.320 --> 00:05:42.550
SEC

00:05:42.550 --> 00:05:42.560
Scott—he

00:05:42.560 --> 00:05:45.230
said

00:05:45.240 --> 00:05:47.270
they want to get the Clarity

00:05:47.280 --> 00:05:49.790
Act done. Basically, he's making an

00:05:49.800 --> 00:05:51.350
announcement saying, 'We've got to get

00:05:51.360 --> 00:05:53.670
this Clarity Act done. You all

00:05:53.670 --> 00:05:53.680
have

00:05:53.680 --> 00:05:55.510
to stop

00:05:55.520 --> 00:05:58.190
delaying.'And

00:05:58.200 --> 00:06:01.350
then the guy that's over Coinbase is

00:06:01.360 --> 00:06:03.550
saying, 'We agree.

00:06:03.560 --> 00:06:07.070
We agree

00:06:07.080 --> 00:06:10.350
it's time to pass the Clarity

00:06:10.350 --> 00:06:10.360
Act.'So

00:06:10.360 --> 00:06:16.270
the Sooner is before this. The Treasury

00:06:16.280 --> 00:06:18.310
Secretary...

00:06:18.320 --> 00:06:20.909
Congress has spent the better part of

00:06:20.919 --> 00:06:24.510
half a decade trying to pass a framework

00:06:24.520 --> 00:06:28.430
to onshore the future of finance.

00:06:28.440 --> 00:06:30.350
And so I said, 'What are we going

00:06:30.360 --> 00:06:32.430
to see in the days ahead? A

00:06:32.440 --> 00:06:34.270
Clarity Act.'That's what

00:06:34.270 --> 00:06:34.280
we're

00:06:34.280 --> 00:06:35.590
going to pray about. We keep praying

00:06:35.600 --> 00:06:38.230
about it and I said I saw the

00:06:38.230 --> 00:06:38.240
boys—Donald

00:06:38.240 --> 00:06:41.150
Trump's sons—with the coins and

00:06:41.160 --> 00:06:42.350
they were dancing and they were going

00:06:42.360 --> 00:06:44.110
into the new building. They had a

00:06:44.120 --> 00:06:46.070
big building and I said I saw the

00:06:46.080 --> 00:06:48.950
building start growing and it doubled

00:06:48.960 --> 00:06:51.510
the building that they had.

00:06:51.520 --> 00:06:52.830
So

00:06:52.840 --> 00:06:54.670
when you're looking into a vision, I

00:06:54.680 --> 00:06:56.190
don't try to add to or take away from

00:06:56.200 --> 00:06:58.110
anything, but what is it talking about?

00:06:58.120 --> 00:07:00.909
Was that building

00:07:00.909 --> 00:07:00.919
their

00:07:00.919 --> 00:07:04.830
real estate empire?

00:07:04.840 --> 00:07:08.190
I tried to

00:07:11.560 --> 00:07:13.190
figure out what the Lord's trying to say

00:07:13.200 --> 00:07:16.190
without being flaky about it.

00:07:16.200 --> 00:07:17.670
But

00:07:17.680 --> 00:07:20.390
when I saw that building standing there

00:07:20.400 --> 00:07:22.510
and it was all the Trump letters, and

00:07:22.520 --> 00:07:24.510
then I saw this new

00:07:24.520 --> 00:07:26.590
tower start to grow and it had digital

00:07:26.600 --> 00:07:29.110
all in it, and it started to make

00:07:29.120 --> 00:07:30.909
the real estate building where they are

00:07:30.919 --> 00:07:32.790
at now look really small compared to

00:07:32.800 --> 00:07:34.390
what they're about to do. And

00:07:34.400 --> 00:07:36.710
Barron came on the

00:07:36.720 --> 00:07:38.230
scene. Now I don't know how far Barron

00:07:38.240 --> 00:07:40.150
has left school, if he's going to

00:07:40.160 --> 00:07:42.710
college or whatever, but I'm sure he is.

00:07:42.720 --> 00:07:44.510
And if he's getting a Master's or

00:07:44.520 --> 00:07:46.870
whatever, who knows? But I know that I

00:07:46.880 --> 00:07:49.150
saw Barron come into the building and

00:07:49.160 --> 00:07:52.230
all of a sudden Barron made the whole

00:07:52.240 --> 00:07:54.230
building start having digital writing on

00:07:54.240 --> 00:07:56.150
it.

00:07:56.160 --> 00:07:57.750
And I saw

00:07:58.640 --> 00:08:01.310
Eric leading

00:08:01.310 --> 00:08:01.320
them

00:08:01.320 --> 00:08:03.790
in. But Barron was the

00:08:03.800 --> 00:08:05.750
mastermind. His mind was

00:08:05.760 --> 00:08:07.070
the one that was running this thing

00:08:07.080 --> 00:08:08.110
more.

00:08:08.120 --> 00:08:09.350
Eric went

00:08:09.360 --> 00:08:11.070
and then all of a sudden

00:08:11.080 --> 00:08:13.550
the building started to come alive.

00:08:13.560 --> 00:08:15.190
If everybody remembers that vision that

00:08:15.200 --> 00:08:18.590
I had about a week ago,

00:08:19.960 --> 00:08:21.270
I just get excited about it when

00:08:21.280 --> 00:08:22.750
they start talking this stuff because

00:08:22.760 --> 00:08:24.790
I'm believing God for a financial

00:08:24.800 --> 00:08:27.190
turnaround for the body of Christ,

00:08:27.200 --> 00:08:28.350
for the wealth of the sinners laid up

00:08:28.360 --> 00:08:30.470
for the righteous. And I believe

00:08:30.480 --> 00:08:32.190
in the name of Jesus, we're going to see

00:08:32.200 --> 00:08:33.870
it sooner than later. I keep standing on

00:08:33.880 --> 00:08:36.230
it. I'm not letting it go. As we hear

00:08:36.240 --> 00:08:37.469
everybody talk about the markets

00:08:37.479 --> 00:08:39.990
crashing and things looking bad—'Oh no,

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:41.550
the sky is falling, Chicken

00:08:41.550 --> 00:08:41.560
Little'—I

00:08:41.560 --> 00:08:44.110
believe that as for me and my

00:08:44.120 --> 00:08:45.070
house, we're going to be blessed and we're going to

00:08:45.080 --> 00:08:46.630
keep

00:08:46.640 --> 00:08:48.350
standing, regardless

00:08:48.360 --> 00:08:51.070
if the Great Depression is going all

00:08:51.080 --> 00:08:54.670
around us and we have a major

00:08:54.670 --> 00:08:54.680
1929-style

00:08:54.680 --> 00:08:58.710
crash. I remember a preacher talking

00:08:58.720 --> 00:09:00.310
and he said, 'During the Great

00:09:00.320 --> 00:09:02.350
Depression, my mom and daddy never went

00:09:02.360 --> 00:09:04.630
without

00:09:04.630 --> 00:09:04.640
anything.'He

00:09:04.640 --> 00:09:06.590
said, 'They always

00:09:06.600 --> 00:09:10.390
tithed. They always gave. They always

00:09:10.400 --> 00:09:12.790
sowed to the church. And God always took

00:09:12.800 --> 00:09:14.270
care of them during the Great

00:09:14.280 --> 00:09:15.829
Depression. They never lacked anything.

00:09:15.839 --> 00:09:17.110
They always made their house payment.

00:09:17.120 --> 00:09:18.910
They always had food on the

00:09:18.920 --> 00:09:21.070
table for us kids. They always had all

00:09:21.070 --> 00:09:21.080
this.'And

00:09:21.080 --> 00:09:23.550
he was talking about how God

00:09:23.560 --> 00:09:25.950
always provided even in the Great

00:09:25.960 --> 00:09:28.470
Depression. Now, if you're talking about

00:09:28.480 --> 00:09:31.030
my granny who was 106 when she went

00:09:31.040 --> 00:09:33.430
home to be with the Lord, they

00:09:33.440 --> 00:09:34.950
struggled. They didn't believe in

00:09:34.960 --> 00:09:36.430
tithing. They didn't believe in giving.

00:09:38.960 --> 00:09:40.150
I don't even think they were

00:09:40.160 --> 00:09:42.310
really good

00:09:42.310 --> 00:09:42.320
Baptists.

00:09:42.320 --> 00:09:43.470
They were Baptist, but I don't even think they were really good Baptists. They were just kind

00:09:43.480 --> 00:09:45.750
of lukewarm Baptists even at that.

00:09:47.840 --> 00:09:50.350
She said, "Brendon, we had to eat

00:09:50.360 --> 00:09:52.070
black crow,

00:09:52.080 --> 00:09:54.030
you know, the big black crows

00:09:54.040 --> 00:09:56.070
flying around in the sky."She goes, "Daddy

00:09:56.080 --> 00:09:57.790
would go out there and shoot those black

00:09:57.800 --> 00:10:00.390
crows and we would eat crow pie,

00:10:00.400 --> 00:10:02.910
blackbird pie, black crow pie, and we

00:10:02.920 --> 00:10:04.390
would try to make it out of

00:10:04.400 --> 00:10:06.750
whatever we had to."Then she goes,

00:10:06.760 --> 00:10:08.550
"And if those became scarce because

00:10:08.560 --> 00:10:10.550
people were killing all the crows off,

00:10:10.560 --> 00:10:12.830
we started eating

00:10:12.830 --> 00:10:12.840
possum."She

00:10:12.840 --> 00:10:14.750
said, "We'd go down in

00:10:14.760 --> 00:10:16.430
the creek beds and look for possums and

00:10:16.430 --> 00:10:16.440
we'd

00:10:16.440 --> 00:10:18.070
start eating possum."I said, "Granny,

00:10:18.080 --> 00:10:19.670
what did possum taste like?"She said, "It

00:10:19.680 --> 00:10:21.270
tastes like gristly, really fatty.

00:10:21.280 --> 00:10:23.670
It was real oily because the

00:10:23.680 --> 00:10:25.790
possum was real greasy."She said, "We

00:10:25.800 --> 00:10:27.630
used to try to fry it because

00:10:27.630 --> 00:10:27.640
we

00:10:27.640 --> 00:10:28.830
were

00:10:28.830 --> 00:10:28.840
starving."She

00:10:28.840 --> 00:10:30.670
goes, "And I'll never forget

00:10:30.680 --> 00:10:31.950
getting those

00:10:31.950 --> 00:10:31.960
flour

00:10:31.960 --> 00:10:35.310
sacks from the feed

00:10:35.320 --> 00:10:37.910
store and Mama

00:10:37.920 --> 00:10:39.750
couldn't give us good clothes and we

00:10:39.760 --> 00:10:41.870
were growing as kids, so she would always

00:10:41.880 --> 00:10:45.190
make us feed store sack

00:10:45.190 --> 00:10:45.200
clothes."Even

00:10:45.200 --> 00:10:47.910
up until Granny went home to be

00:10:47.920 --> 00:10:50.230
with the Lord at 106,

